<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
GeglBuffer

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Abstract Base class for memory buffers.

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
Buffers are the basic memory buffer objects for gegl.  Buffers have an array of
pointers of data banks.  Each bank of a Buffer has a size in bytes. The number
of banks is determined by the Tile and ColorModel that creates the Buffer. The
Buffer has no knowledge of the type of data in the buffer, aside from the
number of banks and the the number of bytes in each buffer. An ImageMgr
implementing swapping would use a subclass of Buffer that can have its data
banks swapped to and from secondary storage.
</para>

